title: Detailed usage of RAM, Swap, VMalloc and other memory areas on Linux
agents: linux
catalog: os/kernel
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check verifies all hard and soft quotas of an EMC Isilon cluster and
 checks each used capacity for exceeding warning and critical thresholds. 
 These thresholds can be configured from a WATO rule for each Isilon cluster
 (not each quota). The status of the service ist {OK} if all quotas are OK
 or is worst of {WARN} or {CRIT} resp. Exceeding quotas are listed as
 multiline output in service view (click on service).

item:
 Isilon Quota

inventory:
 One item per Isilon cluster is being created.

